MAHIKENG - Embattled North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo’s supporters on Wednesday stormed a meeting of the African National Congress (ANC)’s provincial executive committee (PEC). Earlier, a small crowd come out in defence of premier, threatening to derail the 2019 elections if he resigns. WATCH: I await PEC to ask me to resign, says Supra Mahumapelo Mahumapelo says the party's provincial executive committee has to show him the door. He's calling for patience as the PEC meets on Wednesday morning. eNCA